org.cobogw.gwt.user.client
Class Color

java.lang.Object
  org.cobogw.gwt.user.client.Color

public class Color
extends java.lang.Object

This class defines a set of color keywords as a typesafe enumeration as defined in the CSS 2.1 Specification. http://www.w3.org/TR/2007/CR-CSS21-20070719/ and provides similar methods but nog a complete set of methods available in the java.awt.Color.

The list of 17 color keywords is: aqua, black, blue, fuchsia, gray, green, lime, maroon, navy, olive, orange, purple, red, silver, teal, white, and yellow. See also: Cascading Style Sheets Level 2 Revision 1 (CSS 2.1)

The class also provides a list of the X11 colors supported by popular browsers. The resulting list is precisely the same as the SVG 1.0 color keyword names. These colors are defined in this class by their respective numeric color value.

See Also:
http://www.w3.org/TR/2007/CR-CSS21-20070719, http://www.w3.org/TR/2007/CR-CSS21-20070719/syndata.html#color-units, http://www.w3.org/TR/2003/CR-css3-color-20030514/#svg-color

HSBtoRGB

public static Color HSBtoRGB(int hue,
                             int saturation,
                             int brightness)
Converts the components of a color, as specified by the HSB model, to an equivalent set of values for the default RGB model. This method has a slightly different interface than the java.awt.Color version of this method.

The hue component should be a value between 0-360. The saturation and brightness should be an integer between 0-100.

Parameters:
hue - the hue component of the color, between 0-360
saturation - the saturation component of the color, between 0-100
brightness - the brightness component of the color, between 0-100
Returns:
a Color object with the specified hue, saturation, and brightness
